c administration whose history is marked by the numerous power struggles which brought elected officials into conflict with professional bureaucrats. Secondly, she sees it as a large enterprise which was notably influenced by modern management techniques, and finally she shows it to be a working environment shaped by professional relationships. Dagenais provides the first detailed history of a municipal administration in Canada, one that is particularly important as Montreal was at the economic and financial centre of Canada during this crucial period of urban and industrial development.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / State.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356803740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773568037423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773568037/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles